### 3. System Function and Purpose

OpenMRS is an open-source Electronic Health Record platform originally developed to support healthcare delivery in resource-constrained environments. At MyClinic, OpenMRS is the sole electronic health record system — the authoritative source of all patient health information.

The system provides the following primary functions:

**Patient registration and demographic management:** New patient registration, demographic data maintenance, patient search and identification, medical record number assignment and management.

**Clinical encounter documentation:** Encounter creation and documentation for all patient visits, clinical observations, vital signs recording, assessment and plan documentation, referral management.

**Medication management:** Medication prescribing and order management, known allergy recording and alerting, current medication list maintenance, medication history tracking.

**Laboratory order and result management:** Laboratory test ordering, result receipt and storage via integration with the laboratory information system, result review and clinical follow-up documentation.

**Care plan management:** Active problem list maintenance, care plan documentation, chronic disease management tracking, preventive care scheduling.

**Clinical reporting:** Patient population reports, clinical quality metrics, mandatory public health reporting for notifiable conditions.

**User and role management:** User account provisioning, role-based access control configuration, session management, administrative functions.

The system serves as the operational core of MyClinic's clinical function. Clinicians access OpenMRS before, during, and after every patient encounter. Administrative staff use the system for patient registration, scheduling coordination, and operational reporting. The system is in active use during all clinic operating hours and is accessible to authorized remote users through the HTTPS interface when necessary for after-hours clinical review.

